{{Quote|I heard that the graveyard is littered with their pearls, each one worth a fortune. I'll find one for you.''"<br />"''Don't be stupid. Not only is there no graveyard, there's no such thing as a krayt or a pearl. All that you'll find out there are some giant sand beetles that will be more than happy to make a meal out of you.|Patrons in a Tatooine cantina|<ref name="PitS">{{InsiderCite|74|Pearls in the Sand}}</ref>}}
The '''Krayt Graveyard''' was a valley on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]]. It was where many [[Krayt dragon/Legends|krayt dragons]] went to die. The bones of hundreds of these creatures littered the valley floor. When an aged krayt sensed death approaching, it instinctively began the arduous journey to this resting place.<ref name="SWG:KG" /> Tatooine settlers long wondered where these creatures went to die. Due to the extreme danger associated with the dragons, not many were overeager to find out. However, a few brave adventurers did search for the graveyard, hoping to find a fabled [[Krayt dragon pearl/Legends|dragon pearl]]. None were known to have returned.<ref name="SWG:KG2">{{SWGcite|exp=AED|type=loading|Krayt Graveyard|Tatooine}}</ref>

After the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], the scientists [[Dusque Mistflier]] and [[Tendau Nandon]] explored the graveyard during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] and managed to find a krayt dragon egg.<ref name="PitS" /> In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref name="SWG_timeline">{{SWG_timeline}}</ref> a [[Force Adept]] explored the area and collected an ancient [[Force artifact/Legends|Force relic]] for [[Loisya Starkos]].<ref name="SWG:RmR">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=general|Replacing my Robe|Dathomir}}</ref> Later, a spacer visited the graveyard and collected a [[Tchotchee pistol]].<ref name="SWG:RPWMIII">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=collection|Rare Pistol Weapons Mark III}}</ref>

